Rather than returning the ol' "null if not found", in Java 8 there's usefulness of Optional and all it brings to the calling code. And imagine how nice it'd read here:
Optional<ConnectorFolder> possibleSubFolder = findFolder(subFolder, folderId);
if(possibleSubFolder.isPresent()) {
  return possibleSubFolder.get();
}

